# Nova Alembic Migrations

This directory contains Alembic database migration scripts for the Nova Workspace backend.

**Project**: [Nova](https://github.com/deaduramilade/nova-workspace) — AI-native collaborative browser workspace (Phase 4 – Production Readiness).

**Database**: PostgreSQL (via SQLAlchemy 2.0 declarative models in `Backend/app/models/` and `app/core/database.py`).

**Configuration**:
- `alembic.ini` (at Backend root) — script location and logging
- `env.py` — loads application settings (DATABASE_URL from `app.core.config`), ensures all models are imported for `--autogenerate`, sets `target_metadata = Base.metadata`, and includes production polish (compare_type, compare_server_default, empty-migration suppression).

## Typical Usage

From the `Backend/` directory (or project root with appropriate PYTHONPATH):

```bash
# Create a new migration after model changes
alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add new field or table"

# Apply migrations (also performed automatically by docker-entrypoint.sh when RUN_DB_MIGRATIONS=true)
alembic upgrade head

# Roll back one revision
alembic downgrade -1

# Show current revision
alembic current
```

See the root [README.md](../../README.md) and [docs/charter.md](../../docs/charter.md) for the overall project direction, data retention rules (7-day ephemeral data), security model, and architecture.

**Note**: This `README` augments the standard Alembic single-database setup. The original generic note has been replaced with project context for contributors and operators.

